./CHANGELOG.md:7:- Added repo-backed sample-capture service wiring for the sampler rollout: `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` now runs `sample_capture_daemon.py` as `User=user` from the project virtualenv with `Restart=always`, `LimitMEMLOCK=infinity`, and `After`/`Requires` on `cypherclaw-jack.service`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now best-effort starts that service after the AV stack comes up; and `tests/test_cypherclaw_boot_runtime.py` pins both the unit-file contract and the boot-script hook.
./CHANGELOG.md:8:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md` as the missing CCS-033 companion page: it states the sampler's aesthetic goals, names the three core usages (memory of place, self-quotation, curated found-sound library), explains `sw_sampler` as the quintet's memory voice, and defines the intended listener experience plus the five governing principles without duplicating implementation detail; added `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_artistic_intent.py` to pin the document's required sections, artistic concepts, concise length, and sampler-doc cross-links, and linked the new page from the sampler architecture doc and the musicianship roadmap.
./CHANGELOG.md:9:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
./CHANGELOG.md:10:- Updated `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to describe the active quintet direction: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`, and the new `sw_sampler` memory voice; the roadmap now separates landed sampler modules (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `sampler_effects.scd`, anti-pattern checks) from still-pending identity/library/SynthDef convergence so the documentation matches the tree's real partial-rollout state.
./CHANGELOG.md:12:- Closed the server-side gap on the new master-bus sampler controls: added a `master_smooth.scd` SuperCollider source stub for `sw_master_smooth` that declares `sampler_amp` and `sampler_bypass_comp` (both default 1.0) alongside the existing `amp` / `drive` / `warmth` / `reverb` / `room` surface; refactored `start_audio.sh` and `restart_composer.sh` to seed the master node via `senseweave.master_bus.master_bus_s_new_args()` so the boot-time `/s_new sw_master_smooth` arg list stays in lockstep with `DEFAULT_MASTER_BUS_VALUES`; added `tests/test_master_smooth_scd.py` to pin the stub's control declarations and the boot scripts' helper-driven seeding.
./CHANGELOG.md:13:- Hardened sampler buffer cap enforcement: `BufferLoader` now rejects non-positive capacities, routes overflow eviction through `on_sampler_free()` before issuing new `/b_alloc` + `/b_allocRead` traffic, and has a regression test that fills the default 64-buffer pool and verifies the full load/evict cycle.
./CHANGELOG.md:23:- Added post-tonal, spectral, and microtonal material strategies: extended `music_theory.py` with `PitchClassSet`, `spectral_partials`, `quarter_tone_to_freq`, and `just_intonation_chord`; added `extract_spectral_peaks` to `audio_analysis.py` for SenseWeave seeding; and wired `harmonic_planner.py` to return avant-garde strategies when requested by phase/style.
./CHANGELOG.md:30:- Implemented ST1-ST6 of the score-tree songwriting stack end to end: added `piece_commission.py`, `piece_brief.py`, `form_grammar.py`, `score_tree.py`, `recursive_composer.py`, `composition_gate.py`, `tracker_compiler.py`, and `piece_queue.py`; extended `repertoire_memory.py` to store structural score-tree summaries; and rewired `duet_composer.py` so tracker solo mode can commission a piece, build a complete score tree, gate it, compile it into tracker scenes, and precompose the next piece into a small persistent queue instead of treating the tracker as the composer.
./CHANGELOG.md:43:- Fixed a live capture fallback issue that made the sampler lean on a quiet self bus: `room_listener.py` now skips absent named JACK ports and tries direct `jack_rec` fallback ports such as `system:capture_1`, while `sample_dsp_activity.py` now resolves missing `theramini_in` to `contact_mic` / `room_mic` before `self_bus`.
./CHANGELOG.md:54:- Locked the EMSD room sampler to tracker transport: `sample_dsp_activity.py` now emits `transport_trigger_now` / `transport_trigger_key`, `sample_playback_engine.py` uses those keys to launch once per musical bucket instead of only by cooldown, and the face/status layer can now reflect that transport-synchronized sampler execution.
./CHANGELOG.md:56:- Fixed the remaining live self-monitor blackout path: when direct `jack_rec` capture times out, `self_listener.py` now falls back to analyzing a fresh `/tmp/room_capture.wav` clip instead of writing a dark `capture_timeout` state, so glyph and sampler decisions stay audio-derived on boxes where the JACK recorder hangs.
./CHANGELOG.md:60:- Added a replayable musical integration regression that exercises the composer-state -> sampler-plan -> sample-playback -> self-listener glyph state -> face-status chain, so this integration can be verified without a live host.
./CHANGELOG.md:71:- Made the cold-boot meter less ambiguous: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now chooses `SELF_LISTENER_CAPTURE_BACKEND` from the boot-time graph decision, preferring a live PipeWire sink monitor before JACK fallbacks, and it performs a second delayed dedupe pass so late-start room/sampler/face daemons from other boot hooks are collapsed back to one process each.
./CHANGELOG.md:76:- Turned EMSD sample planning into real playback: added `sample_event_renderer.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `sample_status.py`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts the playback daemon; `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` now feeds rendered room-derived WAV events through `pw-play`; and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` exposes the live sampler state for operators and face surfaces.
./CHANGELOG.md:81:- Tightened head-monitor truth again: the sample status line can now read `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` and show actual live sampler playback instead of only the planned source/mode.
./CHANGELOG.md:82:- Made the sampler musically scene-aware instead of only transform-aware: `sample_dsp_activity.py` now emits scene profiles like `development_grains`, `theme_accents`, `recap_echo`, `divination_bed`, and `afterglow_residue`, and `sample_event_renderer.py` now changes duration, density, peak target, filtering, stretch, and echo geometry from those profiles so the room layer follows the tracker form instead of using one generic behavior under different labels.
./CHANGELOG.md:87:- Rebased the EMSD ambient default onto the real room condenser path: Divination/capstone planning and DSP source focus now prefer `room_mic` instead of `garden_mic`, so the default ambient sampler matches the Perform-VE microphone actually present on CypherClaw.
./CHANGELOG.md:90:- Expanded CypherClaw boot coverage for the EMSD sampler path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `theramini_listener.py` and `contact_listener.py` alongside the room listener so the stable sample aliases can refresh during unattended startup instead of remaining planned-but-missing files.
./CHANGELOG.md:106:- Built the first complete M1-M6 musicianship package end to end: added `reharmonizer.py`, `hook_engine.py`, `arrangement_engine.py`, `ear_engine.py`, `practice_curriculum.py`, `prosody_engine.py`, and `repertoire_memory.py`; extended `harmonic_planner.py`, `generative_scores.py`, `music_tracker.py`, `continuous_learner.py`, `duet_composer.py`, and `keyboard_chat.py` so tracker songs now carry section functions, cadence types, hook metadata, scene arrangement intent, practice-block focus, ear-metric evaluation, repertoire storage, and face-visible song titles/captions through the live runtime.
./CHANGELOG.md:120:- Added a mode-aware harmonic planner and live keyboard-grimoire path: tracker solo now preserves major/minor/modal key specs, ignores stale garden and MIDI files, supports scene-level modulation, and `midi_keyboard_listener.py` discovers the real keyboard devices while publishing pedal-derived harmonic suggestions.
