./docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md:44:| `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_buffers.py` | `BufferLoader` — an LRU-bounded scsynth buffer pool. Issues `/b_alloc` and `/b_allocRead` over OSC, evicts the least-recently-used buffer through `on_sampler_free()` when capacity is reached, and returns a stable `bufnum` to the dispatcher. |
./docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md:45:| `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py` | `SamplerDispatcher` — turns a `(SampleRecord, params)` pair into the OSC bundle that triggers the granular voice. Acquires a buffer through the loader, applies the per-mode FX preset, ships `/s_new sw_sampler bufnum=… grain_size=… density=…`, and returns a handle for sustained voices to release later. Folds the per-sample `gain_db` into the synth `amp` so peak-normalized captures play back at consistent loudness. |
./docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md:46:| `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sampler_effects.scd` | SuperCollider source for the `sw_sampler_fx` SynthDef — the dedicated effects bus that sits between the sampler voice and the master bus. Owns the long delay, convolution/FreeVerb reverb, spectral freeze, and the comb resonance tuned to the room's B fundamental (61.74 Hz). |
./docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md:47:| `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/antipatterns.py` | Render-time misuse detection. Hosts `detect_sampler_dominating` and `detect_sampler_silent_quintet_member`, both of which surface through the metrics gate and operator diagnostics. |
