./sdp/logs/Lead_T-028_20260416T181925Z_1776400429.log:41:{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-04-17T04:33:53.351Z","role":"user","content":"<!--\n  sdp-cli agent-specific template for gemini\n  Edit this file to tune how gemini handles lead_t1.md.\n  The shipped default lives at src/sdp/prompts/templates/lead_t1.md.\n  Delete this file to revert to the default.\n-->\n# Task T-028@20260416T181925Z: Implement restraint parameter enforced as global dampener across rules.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- PerformanceIntent.restraint ∈ [0, 1] scales: tempo_deviation_pct (× (1-restraint)), dynamic_range_db (× (1-restraint·0.7)), silence-budget thresholds (× (1 + restraint))<br/>- R2, R10 read restraint at runtime<br/>- tests verify restraint=0 is neutral and restraint=1 produces near-flat phrases with extended silence\n\n**Tier:** T1\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. Read the failing test or bug report to understand the core issue.\n2. Make the minimal code change required to fix the problem.\n3. Run the relevant tests to confirm the fix and ensure no regressions were introduced.\n4. Commit the change with a clear commit message: `fix(scope): summary [T-028@20260416T181925Z]`\n\n## Rules\n\n- Do not expand scope; address only the reported problem.\n- Follow existing code style and patterns.\n- Do not clean, revert, commit, or otherwise normalize unrelated pre-existing\n  workspace changes.\n- Commit your working change immediately.\n\n## Validation\n\nRun this command before finishing:\n```bash\npytest tests/ -x --tb=short && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/\n```\n"}
